		<div class="panel-heading">
    Department of Social Work | Orientation Visit to St. John’s National Academy of Health Sciences
            <b class="panel-title pull-right">June 30<sup>th</sup> 2017</b>
            <div style="clear:both"></div>
        </div>
		<div class="panel-body">
		

			<p align=justify>The Department of Social Work of Kristu Jayanti College, Bangalore has organized an orientation visit for the third semester students to St. John’s National Academy of Health Science on the 27th of June 2017. The students were guided by <b>Dr. I Jerry Richards, Dr. Winne Joyce A. and Dr. Emmanuel Daniel,</b> faculty members, Department of Social work. The orientation visit started with a brief session by <b>Mr. Sachin,</b> Medico Social Worker, to familiarize the role of an Emergency Department in a hospital where grief counselling, crisis intervention, psycho social interventions and other services are provided. This was followed by the presentation on the new approaches and challenges in Medico Social Work by <b>Dr. Eliza Pereira,</b> Head, Department of Social Work St. John’s National Academy of Health Science. <b>Dr. Pereira</b> shared various cases as examples in order to make the students to develop an understanding on the respective topic. The next session was engaged by Ms. Anveera, Medico Social Worker, wherein she discussed the role of a social worker in an Intensive Care Unit which comprised of focusing on emotional support, providing psycho education and medical adherence and so on. The session also included the emotional challenges faced by the care givers, care takers and the family members of the patients admitted in ICU. This session was followed by an appealing theme on Organ Donation and transplant co-ordination which was handled by Mr. Bijo T. Jose, Medico Social Worker, in which he gave an insight on the importance of the role of a transplant co-ordinator in a medical setting. </p>
			<p>In the afternoon session the social work students were taken to the various departments in the hospital like OPD, Emergency department, Nephrology department, dialysis ward, paediatrics department in order to get an exposure to the working environment of these departments. The students also had an opportunity to hear the success stories from the survivors of serious medical cases, which was a great inspiration. The final session was taken by Ms. Kannika, Medico Social Worker, in which she described about the psycho social assessment and intervention and the characteristics and parameters of the psycho social intervention.</p>
			<p>The orientation visit came to an end with a vote of thanks by Ms.Aksa Varghese, II MSW. The social work students had a great learning experience and a quality time at the hospital. </p>



			
